# Model selection

Use Opus 4.6 for implementation work in Cursor.

Use Opus 4.8 for planning and task breakdown.

## Nightshift task briefs

Leave `model` unset in nightshift task briefs by default; an unset model resolves to `auto`, which lets the worker pick the most cost-effective capable model for its backend.

Pin a model only when a task genuinely needs a specific capability — e.g. `model: max` for the most capable configuration the worker can offer (biggest model / max thinking / max context), or an explicit vendor model id (e.g. `claude-opus-4-8`) for planning-grade reasoning.

An explicit, vendor-specific id also routes the task: the manager only offers it to a worker that advertises that model. For automated scheduling (spawn_daily), a pinned id must appear in `scheduled_models_allow` in `config.json` — this is a filter that restricts which models recurring jobs use; the UI model dropdown is populated from live worker registrations.
